#491
On the Drawbridge~
This is the main entranceway into the castle courtyard. It spans the
twenty foot moat which surrounds the entire structure. Made of thick black
wood, the drawbridge is wide and strong enough to support several horsemen
side by side as well as large, heavy siege equipment. A high arched doorway
stands open before you, providing passage through the castle's outer wall.
