#704
The Hall of Statues~
You are in a long, wide hallway, running north and south. The walls are
made of light gray granite, rising fifteen feet, with several small
alcoves along the east and west walls. A life size statue, carved from
marble, occupies each alcove. The ceiling is curved, forming a half
cylinder. Tall torch holders have been placed in between each alcove
and provide a flickering light, causing strange and haunting shadows.
