#782
A Narrow Corridor~
This hallway seems cramped and small compared with the spaceousness of
the rest of the spire. The floor tiles have been carved from dull, gray
stone; fit together with very tight seams.  Decorative, multi-colored
wall hangings cover both sides of the corridor to reduce the draft.
Three braziers burn with a purplish light, centered against the north, east
and west walls.
