Standing On A Ledge~
Digging your finger tips into the spaces between the stone blocks of the
castle wall, and standing on your tip toes on the narrow ledge, you cling
dangerously high above the ground. Looking back over your shoulder, you can
see a massive tower reaching up into the sky. The bottom half appears to
have been destroyed, completely, and now the upper portion remains, floating
in mid air above a lush green courtyard below.  A jagged-edged hole in the
spire's outter wall lies directly behind you, only a few feet away. The
ledge has crumbled away further to the north, making it impossible to
continue.
