#993
The Spire Lookout~
This is a flat, circular platform atop the giant spire.  The open sky is
above you and no railing protects you at the edge of the floor.  In all
directions, the vast contryside is stretched out before you.  To the north
your view follows the River Carthein as it weaves through dense forest on
both sides.  Even farther, the majestic Mt. Vryce stands impassively at the
source of the river, piercing the clouds.  At each cardinal direction, a thick
column rises up seamlessly from the spire's outter wall and form a tall point
over this platform, more than twenty feet above your head.  The echoing of
a lion's roar can be heard in the distance.
~
