#3593
In a Spire~
This is a large, open chamber inside the hollow spire.  Several windows,
large enough for a human to stand upright in, are placed symetrically
around the walls.  A large pile of multi-colored feathers sits against
the southern wall, under one of the windows.  To the north is a large
table made of dull, black wood with a matching padded chair; both appear
to belong to a giant.  Many torch sconces are bolted into the walls about
ten feet off the ground, glowing with a warm blaze.  A large hole in the
center of the floor leads down to the main living chamber while a matching
hole in the ceiling leads up to the roof.
